---
import { SITE } from '../data/site';
---
<section id="about" class="section" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  <div class="container-page">
    <div class="border-y border-line-strong">
      <div class="grid gap-12 py-12 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.15fr)_320px] lg:gap-20">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="mono-label">About</p>
          <h2 id="about-heading" class="display mt-5 text-[clamp(2.5rem,6vw,4.75rem)] text-text">
            Building the boring parts well.
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-8 text-[1.45rem] font-light leading-[1.55] tracking-[-0.03em] text-text">
            I work at the seam between product thinking and implementation: figuring out what an AI or data system should do, what it should not do, and then wiring the thing into a stack that can survive production use.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-lg leading-8 text-muted">
            Most projects eventually come down to clear boundaries, trustworthy pipelines, real evaluation loops, boring infrastructure choices, and interfaces that another engineer can understand without a guided tour.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <div>
            <p class="mono-label">Base</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-text">{SITE.location}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-8 border-t border-line py-10 md:grid-cols-3 reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div>
          <p class="mono-label">01</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-text">Strategy to shipping</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">No handoff gap between defining the work and building the system that delivers it.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="mono-label">02</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-text">Production-grade systems</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">Evals, observability, failure handling, and sensible defaults are part of the build, not cleanup work.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="mono-label">03</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-text">Clear technical writing</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">Architectures, tradeoffs, and deliverables are documented so teams can operate what gets shipped.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
